Render <iframe> embeds in the template README.

The template README is rendered by the shared Markdown component, which uses
react-markdown with no rehype-raw plugin, so any raw HTML (e.g. an <iframe>
interactive-guide embed) in README.md is silently dropped. Add an opt-in
`allowEmbeds` prop, enabled only by TemplateDocsPage, that turns on a scoped
raw-HTML pipeline: rehype-raw parses the HTML, then rehype-sanitize strips
everything not described by embedSchema (the defaults plus a tightly scoped
<iframe> and the inline style responsive wrappers need).

Which iframe hosts may actually load is enforced by the browser via Coder's
existing frame-src CSP (set per deployment with CODER_ADDITIONAL_CSP_POLICY),
so no separate host allowlist is maintained in the frontend. Every other
Markdown consumer keeps the strict, no-raw-HTML default.

